## CSS File Location and Toolbar Styling

The editor toolbar CSS is defined in:
**`/c/Users/johnm/iskrib_v3/client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/editor.css`**

### Toolbar Container CSS (Lines 192-223)

**`.toolbar-wrapper`** (lines 193-204) - The outer container:
```css
.toolbar-wrapper {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--editor-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--editor-border);
    padding: 0.35rem 0;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 5;
    background-color: var(--editor-bg);
}
```

**`.toolbar`** (lines 205-211) - The main toolbar flex container:
```css
.toolbar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2px;
    width: 100%;
    flex-wrap: wrap;  /* Allows wrapping on desktop */
}
```

### Mobile Responsive Styles (Lines 1064-1142)

The critical mobile overrides for overflow and scrolling are in the media query `@media (max-width: 640px)`:

**Mobile toolbar** (lines 1075-1083):
```css
.toolbar {
    flex-wrap: nowrap;                    /* Changes from wrap to no-wrap */
    overflow-x: auto;                     /* Horizontal scroll enabled */
    scrollbar-width: none;                /* Hide scrollbar (Firefox) */
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;    /* Smooth momentum scrolling (iOS) */
}
.toolbar::-webkit-scrollbar {
    display: none;                        /* Hide scrollbar (Chrome/Safari) */
}
```

**Fade-out gradient** (lines 1087-1097) - `.toolbar-wrapper::after`:
```css
.toolbar-wrapper::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 24px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--editor-bg, var(--bg-elevated)));
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 6;
}
```

**Mobile button sizing** (lines 1098-1108):
```css
.toolbar-bttns,
.is-active {
    padding: 0.55rem;
    min-width: 36px;
    min-height: 36px;
}
.toolbar-bttns svg,
.is-active svg {
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
}
```

### Key Features Summary

| Property | Desktop | Mobile |
|----------|---------|--------|
| **flex-wrap** | wrap | nowrap |
| **overflow-x** | (inherits) | auto (scrollable) |
| **Scrollbar** | Visible (thin) | Hidden (none) |
| **Mobile touch** | N/A | smooth momentum (-webkit-overflow-scrolling) |
| **Fade gradient** | None | 24px linear gradient on right edge |
| **Button padding** | 0.4rem | 0.55rem (larger touch targets) |
| **Position** | sticky, top: 0 | Same (sticky positioning maintained) |

The design uses a gradient fade-out effect on mobile to indicate scrollable content and hides the scrollbar for a cleaner appearance while maintaining momentum scrolling on iOS devices.
